#behindthescenes #timelapse #illustration

Quick Treat: Mega S’more! 😂🍫

This was quite the balancing act to make but also a lot of fun! Always love combining a little drawing with stop motion. #stopmotion #animation

Lunar Bamboo Forest 🌸🍃🎋

In the distance, a strange phenomenon occurred. A bamboo forest grew in the void of space, defying all laws of physics and biology. The forest was so large and dense that it could be seen from far away by any passing spaceship. They glimmered with a soft, green light that filled the surrounding darkness. But the most unusual thing about the forest was its inhabitants.

Gross, there was a worm in my coffee. 🤮🪱 ☕️ 

#stopmotion #animation #stopmotionanimation

I always have fun doing transforming stop motion animations. In order to get close to the color of the gloves I mixed blue, purple, and white clay. With mixing the clay, it heats up from my hands and makes it way easier to work with while animating.

I’ve been enjoying the process of starting 2D and going all the way to a physical object. Each step makes me think differently. From the digital sketching, to 3D sculpting, to 3D printing, and finally the painting. Each one challenges me in different ways. #3dprinting #3dsculpt #resinart

Resin Pouring + 3D Resin Printing 
This has been a technique I’ve wanted to test out and I finally got to. 🌸

There were some mistakes I made with mixing the resin like not mixing properly, stirring to fast, etc. Some of the reasons for the bubbles. All good though because now I know what to do on future sculptures! #3dprinting #resinart #3dsculpting

It was fun to 3D sculpt this more detailed graphic using some pastel colors. I tend to lean towards more bolder colors, but I liked the softer colors with the round 3D shapes. #3Dsculpting #3D #sculpt

Floating Garden Resin Sculpture 🌸- Absolutely everything in this was made from resin. Started from sculpting the models in C4D. I then brought it into Lychee to prepare for 3D printing. Next I 3D printed the flowers which took roughly 5 hrs. I began to airbrush the flower prints with some bright colors which I also used in a stop motion. Once all of that was complete, I began to pour the resin block. This took roughly the whole day to layer and create. This is my best resin pouring to date, so I’m super pumped. #resinart #resincraft #3dprinting

Excited to showcase the Midnight Daisy Bracelet that will be available on January 5th at 7 pm EST on the @petalheadz website. The website is currently under construction.

This first round of bracelets will be a small batch so will more than likely go quickly! Each bracelet will include some vinyl stickers as well!

Each center bead is made from resin that is sculpted by me. The thicker elastic string allows for a durable stretch for different wrist sizes. 

Other items will be available including 1/1 resin sculptures, clothing, and the Fine China Petal.
